       ctoken strvar separators

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       Parses  a  token out of a character string.  The string to
       parse is contained in  the  variable  named  strvar.   The
       string  separators  contains  all  of  the valid separator
       characters for tokens in the string.  All leading  separa-
       tors  are  skipped  and  the first token is returned.  The
       variable strvar will be modified to contain the  remainder
       of the string following the token.

